<br>
Some people in United Guilds of Drinal (UGoD) have asked me about raiding VS.  I'm of the opinion that with the forces we can currently bring to take down stuff like Treah in PoG, we can do VS...I'm a little worried about that whole Lifetap thing, but I think he's a good stepping stone mob for us to try as we get closer to being able to take a shot at bigger stuff like Trak.  However, I don't know how contested his spawns are nowadays...I know there used to be a list ages ago, and I imagine some of the guilds who used to do him have moved on to tougher mobs, but could someone from CT/TK/KC/9C/whoever is killing him fill me in on how you guys share VS?  Does he usually just go down right after a patch by whoever gets there first?  Tactics advice isn't necessary, I don't mind it of course, but I'm not asking for your secrets, just if there's any formal sharing of VS spawns or whatever.<br>
<br>
/shrug...just looking for info for now, no raids scheduled yet <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Seke Darktower<br>
54 Rogue, Phoenix Order<br>
Chairman, United Guilds of Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/umeneldil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meneldil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 356<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 10:57:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> heres what you do when you want a spawn like VS, you tell everyone to camp out at Karnor the night before a patch.  When servers up you pull 24+ people into the zone.  If your raiding party is the first 24+ in the zone you have rights to that mob until you decide to leave the zone.  No schedule , no calendar, nothing.  Just be fast and organized and you will suceed.  <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Meneldil Magnus</b><br>
Conjurer of <A href="http://home.the-web-ac.com/jedi" target="_blank">Winter's Light</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 11:12:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> His spawn time is 1 week right?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ukalledar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalledar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 12:55:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> CT hasn't done VS in a long time. I think CT/WL/KC/CiH are mostly doing ToV for superior legs. I agree with Meneldil, if you want VS, camp out in karnor before patch, or time his spawn after he's been killed and gather people there before he spawns so you can claim it.<br>
<br>
VS is easy, but fighting him is vastly different than fighting Treah Greenroot. <p><B><I><FONT FACE="verdana"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="880020">Ji<FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="770560">ng</FONT><BR>60 Or<FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="770560">ac</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="700980">le </FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="661290">of</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="6115a0"> Dr</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="5519c1">in</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="4824d8">al</FONT></FONT><BR></B></I><BR>
<B><I><FONT FACE="verdana"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="880020">Kal<FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="770560">le</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="700980">dar</FONT><BR>53 Gar<FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="770560">den </FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="700980">Wea</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="661290">sel </FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="631495">of</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="6115a0"> Dr</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="5519c1">in</FONT><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="4824d8">al</FONT></FONT><BR></B></I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ulernz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LernZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sissy Wizzy</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 1:20:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> CiH doesn't kill VS.  We have led 1 or 2 pickup raids against him for fun late at night, and also a couple weeks ago to see if we could do him with less then 3 groups.  If your guild/raid is able to hunt in pog, then I suggest you ignore VS for legs.  If you want him for epic pieces thats a different story. <p>Lern Cyberton <br>
lvl 60 Wizard <br>
Officer of Cats in Hats - Drinal <br>
http://www.catsinhats.net</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 8:05:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   VS</span><hr size=1> Its not really a matter of killing him specifically for the legs, though I'm sure that they would make some people very happy...its more for the experience of killing him.  And while UGoD does hit PoG at least once or twice a week, we mostly hunt west of the river and often don't get to pulling a lot of the leg/bp mobs except those near the Lake.  <br>
<br>
Also, VS is a mob where agro management is crucial, and I think UGoD needs more experiences like that.  I mean, most of stuff we do is zerg-rushing cause we're not fighting many mobs where ping-ponging = instant death, and if we're going to ever be able to take on some of the real Velious uber mobs, we're gonna have to improve on our tactics.<br>
<br>
Seke <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ualealthewiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aleal the Wiz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://portnoy.uninterruptible.com/~fuellg/tz.gif height=20 width=20 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 10:05:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: VS</span><hr size=1> VS owned with 11 people~  Not quiet sure what the 24 thing is, its whatever you need to kill the mob.  I think Valindor said like 12 for severilious was enough(that would be tough) so I dunno what VS's magic number would be.<br>
<br>
I read on some post on UGOD board that they were tough enough to lock everyone else out from every other spawn.  If so, why isn't VS on your list?   <p>Aleal the Tactician - High Sorceress of Neriak</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udocnurse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Docnurse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 10:25:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: VS</span><hr size=1> Make sure the highest level warrior is main tanks hand have him gain agg and try and hold it. Then start nuking at 60% if your wizards start to soon and he starts killing of the casters your chance of winning drops down by a lot. Hope you guys do well and if you have any questions just ask.<br>
<br>
Enursin Officer of Crimson Twilight  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/unoddaduma.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nodda Duma </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 10:35:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wsphotofews.excite.com/002/7O/UE/aN/7V68762.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: VS</span><hr size=1> <br>
if that don't work, try bum-rush and beating the everliving shit outta him.  thing with VS is you gotta drop him fast~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uaakla2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>aakla2</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=ttp://www.geocities.com/aakla2/EQ000014.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 290<br> <font color=#939393>(8/21/01 10:36:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re:</span><hr size=1> theonly strategy for VS is Dog Pile.throw everyone you have at time and use the highest damageing skill you have. if the fight last more then about 17 seconds your doing something wrong. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uterok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Terok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#939393>(8/22/01 1:40:19 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.tir.com/~jtcable/blacksquare.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> -Rune<br>
-Wizards<br>
-Offensive Disciplines<br>
<br>
Rune stops the lifetap from landing, meaning he doesn't get any hit points back from it. If everybody is runed, and you have enough damage there, chances are he won't even get to tap. If you want to do more &quot;main tanking&quot; stuff, just chain rune the main tank. <br>
<br>
Wizards can manage to do quick damage to him. He only has like 16k hit points I think, so unless you have a bunch of level 60 melees wailing on him, wizards can be very key in the damage.<br>
<br>
Offensive Disciplines are the way to go on this guy. Just burn everything you have from the start. He'll go down faster than *insert random guild mate* on *insert random event/day* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#939393>(8/22/01 6:22:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> Uhm, Aleal, can you direct me to the post where someone claimed UGoD was tough enough to lock people out of spawns?  *chuckle*  That's rich.  I think we could lock down orc1 and orc2 pretty well, and maybe even the derv camp in WC...at least, that's what it feels like when I compare what we do to what CiH does.<br>
<br>
Seke <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ualealthewiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aleal the Wiz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://portnoy.uninterruptible.com/~fuellg/tz.gif height=20 width=20 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 508<br> <font color=#939393>(8/22/01 8:24:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> Some post about Nag/Vox on your board after Vlladimr? led a raid or something. <p>Aleal the Tactician - High Sorceress of Neriak</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#939393>(8/22/01 9:08:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> Oh...Naggy and Vox, what a nightmare that pair is, every dispute we have in UGoD seems to be in some way related to them.  /shrug, yeah, I suppose we would be capable of locking those down if we wanted to, but its kinda pointless because:<br>
A) our raids are open, pick-up style raids usually, so I don't know who we would be locking out<br>
B) most of us aren't dicks<br>
C) i try to make people who want to lead Naggy/Vox raids aware of our boards to get them involved<br>
<br>
In theory, sure, UGoD could lock down some spawns and stuff like that, but we have no reason to do so.  Its not our style at all.  We're trying to get a dragon reservation list going for them, and while I'm sure there will be &quot;snipes&quot; by people who aren't aware that they are sniping, hopefully we can bring them into the UGoD community and get them working with us.<br>
<br>
Seke <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/umeneldil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meneldil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 357<br> <font color=#939393>(8/22/01 10:21:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> B) most of us aren't dicks<br>
<br>
<br>
your on the wrong server buddy<br>
<br>
<br>
edit: just a joke =)  We have a server full of fun loving get-along people!  One big happy bundle of love called Drinal! =P<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Meneldil Magnus</b><br>
Conjurer of <A href="http://home.the-web-ac.com/jedi" target="_blank">Winter's Light</A></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/umeneldil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meneldil</A> at: 8/22/01 10:32:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#939393>(8/22/01 11:26:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> /shrug...most of the people in UGoD guilds I have interacted with really aren't dicks.  And since I'm vaguely in charge of the whole deal, I've interacted with most of them.  We definitely have our rotten eggs, our egotistical raid leaders, our loot hogs, etc., but for the most part, people are very willing to help others, respect others, do whats best for the group, etc.--traits and behaviors I find to be pretty indicative of non-dickishness (my new word for the day).<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ufflewddurfflam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fflewddur Fflam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#939393>(8/22/01 12:15:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Venril Sathir</span><hr size=1> Just make sure if you allow a lot of tanks to melee him that they are all runed and have disciplines to avoid the lifetap proc.  Nothing quite like losing because he continually riposted lifetap on 17 paladins, sk's and rangers...<br>
<br>
-FF <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showMessage?topicID=1851.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showMessage?topicID=1814.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.threadControl?topicID=1850.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1850.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1850.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub28.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="drinal28133frm1">General<option value="drinal28133frm2">Trading<option value="drinal28133frm9">Quests<option value="drinal28133frm10">Screenshots<option value="drinal28133frm11">Role-playing<option value="drinal28133frm12">Flames<option value="drinal28133frm17">Guild Information<option value="drinal28133frm4">Hate Raids<option value="drinal28133frm5">Fear Raids<option value="drinal28133frm6">Sky Raids<option value="drinal28133frm21">Growth Raids<option value="drinal28133frm22">Mischief Raids<option value="drinal28133frm20">Dragon Raids<option value="drinal28133frm16">Suggestions - Forums & Webpage<option value="drinal28133frm23">Epic Quest Raids<option value="drinal28133frm24">MISC Raids<option valu